<g data-node-id="so-virgin-def"><rect class="nbcr" x="60" y="110" width="1480" height="100" rx="14"/><text x="90" y="148" font-family="Inter,system-ui,sans-serif" font-size="16" font-weight="800" fill="#8B6914">👰 VIRGINITY — Definitions</text><text x="90" y="180" font-family="Inter,system-ui,sans-serif" font-size="14" font-weight="500" fill="#5C4810">★ <strong>VIRGIN:</strong> A female who has never had sexual intercourse. ★ <strong>DEFLORATED:</strong> Loss of virginity. ★ <strong>FALSE VIRGIN:</strong> Female who has had sexual intercourse but hymen is INTACT (hymen elastic, fleshy, yielding type). Medicolegal importance — opinion on virginity is RELATIVE and based on multiple signs, not hymen alone.</text><circle class="ic" cx="1500" cy="130" r="14"/><text class="t-info" x="1500" y="136" text-anchor="middle">ⓘ</text></g>

