<g data-node-id="so-hymen-anatomy"><rect class="nbcr" x="60" y="110" width="1480" height="130" rx="14"/><text x="90" y="148" font-family="Inter,system-ui,sans-serif" font-size="16" font-weight="800" fill="#8B6914">🔬 HYMEN — Anatomy</text><text x="90" y="180" font-family="Inter,system-ui,sans-serif" font-size="14" font-weight="500" fill="#5C4810">★ Hymen = thin but firm fold of <strong>CONNECTIVE TISSUE</strong> lined on both sides by <strong>STRATIFIED SQUAMOUS EPITHELIUM</strong>. About <strong>1 mm thickness</strong>. Situated at the <strong>VAGINAL ORIFICE</strong>.</text><text x="90" y="210" font-family="Inter,system-ui,sans-serif" font-size="14" font-weight="500" fill="#5C4810">Developmentally a remnant of the <strong>vaginal plates</strong> between Mullerian duct and cloaca. ★ Has NO useful physiological function.</text><circle class="ic" cx="1500" cy="130" r="14"/><text class="t-info" x="1500" y="136" text-anchor="middle">ⓘ</text></g>

